PJSUA

This is the reference implementation for PJSIP and PJMEDIA. PJSUA is a console based application, designed to be simple enough to be readble, but powerful enough to demonstrate all features available in PJSIP and PJMEDIA.

This file is pjsip-apps/src/pjsua/pjsua_app.c

70 static void ringback_start(pjsua_call_id call_id)
71 {
72  if (app_config.no_tones)
73  return;
74 
75  if (app_config.call_data[call_id].ringback_on)
76  return;
77 
78  app_config.call_data[call_id].ringback_on = PJ_TRUE;
79 
80  if (++app_config.ringback_cnt==1 &&
81  app_config.ringback_slot!=PJSUA_INVALID_ID)
82  {
83  pjsua_conf_connect(app_config.ringback_slot, 0);
84  }
85 }

87 static void ring_stop(pjsua_call_id call_id)
88 {
89  if (app_config.no_tones)
90  return;
91 
92  if (app_config.call_data[call_id].ringback_on) {
93  app_config.call_data[call_id].ringback_on = PJ_FALSE;
94 
95  pj_assert(app_config.ringback_cnt>0);
96  if (--app_config.ringback_cnt == 0 &&
97  app_config.ringback_slot!=PJSUA_INVALID_ID)
98  {
99  pjsua_conf_disconnect(app_config.ringback_slot, 0);
100  pjmedia_tonegen_rewind(app_config.ringback_port);
101  }
102  }
103 
104  if (app_config.call_data[call_id].ring_on) {
105  app_config.call_data[call_id].ring_on = PJ_FALSE;
106 
107  pj_assert(app_config.ring_cnt>0);
108  if (--app_config.ring_cnt == 0 &&
109  app_config.ring_slot!=PJSUA_INVALID_ID)
110  {
111  pjsua_conf_disconnect(app_config.ring_slot, 0);
112  pjmedia_tonegen_rewind(app_config.ring_port);
113  }
114  }
115 }

134 /* Callback from timer when the maximum call duration has been
135  * exceeded.
136  */
137 static void call_timeout_callback(pj_timer_heap_t *timer_heap,
138  struct pj_timer_entry *entry)
139 {
140  pjsua_call_id call_id = entry->id;
141  pjsua_msg_data msg_data_;
142  pjsip_generic_string_hdr warn;
143  pj_str_t hname = pj_str("Warning");
144  pj_str_t hvalue = pj_str("399 pjsua \"Call duration exceeded\"");
145 
146  PJ_UNUSED_ARG(timer_heap);
147 
148  if (call_id == PJSUA_INVALID_ID) {
149  PJ_LOG(1,(THIS_FILE, "Invalid call ID in timer callback"));
150  return;
151  }
152 
153  /* Add warning header */
154  pjsua_msg_data_init(&msg_data_);
155  pjsip_generic_string_hdr_init2(&warn, &hname, &hvalue);
156  pj_list_push_back(&msg_data_.hdr_list, &warn);
157 
158  /* Call duration has been exceeded; disconnect the call */
159  PJ_LOG(3,(THIS_FILE, "Duration (%d seconds) has been exceeded "
160  "for call %d, disconnecting the call",
161  app_config.duration, call_id));
162  entry->id = PJSUA_INVALID_ID;
163  pjsua_call_hangup(call_id, 200, NULL, &msg_data_);
164 }

166 /*
167  * Handler when invite state has changed.
168  */
169 static void on_call_state(pjsua_call_id call_id, pjsip_event *e)
170 {
171  pjsua_call_info call_info;
172 
173  PJ_UNUSED_ARG(e);
174 
175  pjsua_call_get_info(call_id, &call_info);
176 
177  if (call_info.state == PJSIP_INV_STATE_DISCONNECTED) {
178 
179  /* Stop all ringback for this call */
180  ring_stop(call_id);
181 
182  /* Cancel duration timer, if any */
183  if (app_config.call_data[call_id].timer.id != PJSUA_INVALID_ID) {
184  app_call_data *cd = &app_config.call_data[call_id];
185  pjsip_endpoint *endpt = pjsua_get_pjsip_endpt();
186 
187  cd->timer.id = PJSUA_INVALID_ID;
188  pjsip_endpt_cancel_timer(endpt, &cd->timer);
189  }
190 
191  /* Rewind play file when hangup automatically,
192  * since file is not looped
193  */
194  if (app_config.auto_play_hangup)
195  pjsua_player_set_pos(app_config.wav_id, 0);
196 
197 
198  PJ_LOG(3,(THIS_FILE, "Call %d is DISCONNECTED [reason=%d (%.*s)]",
199  call_id,
200  call_info.last_status,
201  (int)call_info.last_status_text.slen,
202  call_info.last_status_text.ptr));
203 
204  if (call_id == current_call) {
205  find_next_call();
206  }
207 
208  /* Dump media state upon disconnected.
209  * Now pjsua_media_channel_deinit() automatically log the call dump.
210  */
211  if (0) {
212  PJ_LOG(5,(THIS_FILE,
213  "Call %d disconnected, dumping media stats..",
214  call_id));
215  log_call_dump(call_id);
216  }
217 
218  } else {
219 
220  if (app_config.duration != PJSUA_APP_NO_LIMIT_DURATION &&
221  call_info.state == PJSIP_INV_STATE_CONFIRMED)
222  {
223  /* Schedule timer to hangup call after the specified duration */
224  app_call_data *cd = &app_config.call_data[call_id];
225  pjsip_endpoint *endpt = pjsua_get_pjsip_endpt();
226  pj_time_val delay;
227 
228  cd->timer.id = call_id;
229  delay.sec = app_config.duration;
230  delay.msec = 0;
231  pjsip_endpt_schedule_timer(endpt, &cd->timer, &delay);
232  }
233 
234  if (call_info.state == PJSIP_INV_STATE_EARLY) {
235  int code;
236  pj_str_t reason;
237  pjsip_msg *msg;
238 
239  /* This can only occur because of TX or RX message */
240  pj_assert(e->type == PJSIP_EVENT_TSX_STATE);
241 
242  if (e->body.tsx_state.type == PJSIP_EVENT_RX_MSG) {
243  msg = e->body.tsx_state.src.rdata->msg_info.msg;
244  } else {
245  msg = e->body.tsx_state.src.tdata->msg;
246  }
247 
248  code = msg->line.status.code;
249  reason = msg->line.status.reason;
250 
251  /* Start ringback for 180 for UAC unless there's SDP in 180 */
252  if (call_info.role==PJSIP_ROLE_UAC && code==180 &&
253  msg->body == NULL &&
254  call_info.media_status==PJSUA_CALL_MEDIA_NONE)
255  {
256  ringback_start(call_id);
257  }
258 
259  PJ_LOG(3,(THIS_FILE, "Call %d state changed to %.*s (%d %.*s)",
260  call_id, (int)call_info.state_text.slen,
261  call_info.state_text.ptr, code,
262  (int)reason.slen, reason.ptr));
263  } else {
264  PJ_LOG(3,(THIS_FILE, "Call %d state changed to %.*s",
265  call_id,
266  (int)call_info.state_text.slen,
267  call_info.state_text.ptr));
268  }
269 
270  if (current_call==PJSUA_INVALID_ID)
271  current_call = call_id;
272 
273  }
274 }

297 static void on_incoming_call(pjsua_acc_id acc_id, pjsua_call_id call_id,
298  pjsip_rx_data *rdata)
299 {
300  pjsua_call_info call_info;
301 
302  PJ_UNUSED_ARG(acc_id);
303  PJ_UNUSED_ARG(rdata);
304 
305  pjsua_call_get_info(call_id, &call_info);
306 
307  if (current_call==PJSUA_INVALID_ID)
308  current_call = call_id;
309 
310 #ifdef USE_GUI
311  showNotification(call_id);
312 #endif
313 
314  /* Start ringback */
315  if (call_info.rem_aud_cnt)
316  ring_start(call_id);
317 
318  if (app_config.auto_answer > 0) {
319  pjsua_call_setting opt;
320 
321  pjsua_call_setting_default(&opt);
322  opt.aud_cnt = app_config.aud_cnt;
323  opt.vid_cnt = app_config.vid.vid_cnt;
324 
325  pjsua_call_answer2(call_id, &opt, app_config.auto_answer, NULL,
326  NULL);
327  }
328 
329  if (app_config.auto_answer < 200) {
330  char notif_st[80] = {0};
331 
332 #if PJSUA_HAS_VIDEO
333  if (call_info.rem_offerer && call_info.rem_vid_cnt) {
334  snprintf(notif_st, sizeof(notif_st),
335  "To %s the video, type \"vid %s\" first, "
336  "before answering the call!\n",
337  (app_config.vid.vid_cnt? "reject":"accept"),
338  (app_config.vid.vid_cnt? "disable":"enable"));
339  }
340 #endif
341 
342  PJ_LOG(3,(THIS_FILE,
343  "Incoming call for account %d!\n"
344  "Media count: %d audio & %d video\n"
345  "%s"
346  "From: %.*s\n"
347  "To: %.*s\n"
348  "Press %s to answer or %s to reject call",
349  acc_id,
350  call_info.rem_aud_cnt,
351  call_info.rem_vid_cnt,
352  notif_st,
353  (int)call_info.remote_info.slen,
354  call_info.remote_info.ptr,
355  (int)call_info.local_info.slen,
356  call_info.local_info.ptr,
357  (app_config.use_cli?"ca a":"a"),
358  (app_config.use_cli?"g":"h")));
359  }

362 /* General processing for media state. "mi" is the media index */
363 static void on_call_generic_media_state(pjsua_call_info *ci, unsigned mi,
364  pj_bool_t *has_error)
365 {
366  const char *status_name[] = {
367  "None",
368  "Active",
369  "Local hold",

371  "Error"
372  };
373 
374  PJ_UNUSED_ARG(has_error);
375 
376  pj_assert(ci->media[mi].status <= PJ_ARRAY_SIZE(status_name));
377  pj_assert(PJSUA_CALL_MEDIA_ERROR == 4);
378 
379  PJ_LOG(4,(THIS_FILE, "Call %d media %d [type=%s], status is %s",
380  ci->id, mi, pjmedia_type_name(ci->media[mi].type),
381  status_name[ci->media[mi].status]));
382 }

384 /* Process audio media state. "mi" is the media index. */
385 static void on_call_audio_state(pjsua_call_info *ci, unsigned mi,
386  pj_bool_t *has_error)
387 {
388  PJ_UNUSED_ARG(has_error);
389 
390  /* Stop ringback */
391  ring_stop(ci->id);
392 
393  /* Connect ports appropriately when media status is ACTIVE or REMOTE HOLD,
394  * otherwise we should NOT connect the ports.
395  */
396  if (ci->media[mi].status == PJSUA_CALL_MEDIA_ACTIVE ||
397  ci->media[mi].status == PJSUA_CALL_MEDIA_REMOTE_HOLD)
398  {
399  pj_bool_t connect_sound = PJ_TRUE;
400  pj_bool_t disconnect_mic = PJ_FALSE;
401  pjsua_conf_port_id call_conf_slot;
402 
403  call_conf_slot = ci->media[mi].stream.aud.conf_slot;
404 
405  /* Make sure conf slot is valid (e.g: media dir is not "inactive") */
406  if (call_conf_slot == PJSUA_INVALID_ID)
407  return;
408 
409  /* Loopback sound, if desired */
410  if (app_config.auto_loop) {
411  pjsua_conf_connect(call_conf_slot, call_conf_slot);
412  connect_sound = PJ_FALSE;
413  }
414 
415  /* Automatically record conversation, if desired */
416  if (app_config.auto_rec && app_config.rec_port != PJSUA_INVALID_ID) {
417  pjsua_conf_connect(call_conf_slot, app_config.rec_port);
418  }
419 
420  /* Stream a file, if desired */
421  if ((app_config.auto_play || app_config.auto_play_hangup) &&
422  app_config.wav_port != PJSUA_INVALID_ID)
423  {
424  pjsua_conf_connect(app_config.wav_port, call_conf_slot);
425  connect_sound = PJ_FALSE;
426  }
427 
428  /* Stream AVI, if desired */
429  if (app_config.avi_auto_play &&
430  app_config.avi_def_idx != PJSUA_INVALID_ID &&
431  app_config.avi[app_config.avi_def_idx].slot != PJSUA_INVALID_ID)
432  {
433  pjsua_conf_connect(app_config.avi[app_config.avi_def_idx].slot,
434  call_conf_slot);
435  disconnect_mic = PJ_TRUE;
436  }
437 
438  /* Put call in conference with other calls, if desired */
439  if (app_config.auto_conf) {
440  pjsua_call_id call_ids[PJSUA_MAX_CALLS];
441  unsigned call_cnt=PJ_ARRAY_SIZE(call_ids);
442  unsigned i;
443 
444  /* Get all calls, and establish media connection between
445  * this call and other calls.
446  */
447  pjsua_enum_calls(call_ids, &call_cnt);
448 
449  for (i=0; i<call_cnt; ++i) {
450  if (call_ids[i] == ci->id)
451  continue;
452 
453  if (!pjsua_call_has_media(call_ids[i]))
454  continue;
455 
456  pjsua_conf_connect(call_conf_slot,
457  pjsua_call_get_conf_port(call_ids[i]));
458  pjsua_conf_connect(pjsua_call_get_conf_port(call_ids[i]),
459  call_conf_slot);
460 
461  /* Automatically record conversation, if desired */
462  if (app_config.auto_rec && app_config.rec_port !=
463  PJSUA_INVALID_ID)
464  {
465  pjsua_conf_connect(pjsua_call_get_conf_port(call_ids[i]),
466  app_config.rec_port);
467  }
468 
469  }
470 
471  /* Also connect call to local sound device */
472  connect_sound = PJ_TRUE;
473  }
474 
475  /* Otherwise connect to sound device */
476  if (connect_sound) {
477  pjsua_conf_connect(call_conf_slot, 0);
478  if (!disconnect_mic)
479  pjsua_conf_connect(0, call_conf_slot);
480 
481  /* Automatically record conversation, if desired */
482  if (app_config.auto_rec && app_config.rec_port != PJSUA_INVALID_ID)
483  {
484  pjsua_conf_connect(call_conf_slot, app_config.rec_port);
485  pjsua_conf_connect(0, app_config.rec_port);
486  }
487  }
488  }
489 }

503 /*
504  * Callback on media state changed event.
505  * The action may connect the call to sound device, to file, or
506  * to loop the call.
507  */
508 static void on_call_media_state(pjsua_call_id call_id)
509 {
510  pjsua_call_info call_info;
511  unsigned mi;
512  pj_bool_t has_error = PJ_FALSE;
513 
514  pjsua_call_get_info(call_id, &call_info);
515 
516  for (mi=0; mi<call_info.media_cnt; ++mi) {
517  on_call_generic_media_state(&call_info, mi, &has_error);
518 
519  switch (call_info.media[mi].type) {
520  case PJMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO:
521  on_call_audio_state(&call_info, mi, &has_error);
522  break;
523  case PJMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO:
524  on_call_video_state(&call_info, mi, &has_error);
525  break;
526  default:
527  /* Make gcc happy about enum not handled by switch/case */
528  break;
529  }
530  }
531 
532  if (has_error) {
533  pj_str_t reason = pj_str("Media failed");
534  pjsua_call_hangup(call_id, 500, &reason, NULL);
535  }
536 
537 #if PJSUA_HAS_VIDEO
538  /* Check if remote has just tried to enable video */
539  if (call_info.rem_offerer && call_info.rem_vid_cnt)
540  {
541  int vid_idx;
542 
543  /* Check if there is active video */
544  vid_idx = pjsua_call_get_vid_stream_idx(call_id);
545  if (vid_idx == -1 || call_info.media[vid_idx].dir == PJMEDIA_DIR_NONE) {
546  PJ_LOG(3,(THIS_FILE,
547  "Just rejected incoming video offer on call %d, "
548  "use \"vid call enable %d\" or \"vid call add\" to "
549  "enable video!", call_id, vid_idx));
550  }
551  }
552 #endif
553 }

584  call_id, info->digit, duration, method));

590 static pjsip_redirect_op call_on_redirected(pjsua_call_id call_id,

610  }
611

625 /*
626  * Handler for incoming presence subscription request
627  */
628 static void on_incoming_subscribe(pjsua_acc_id acc_id,
629  pjsua_srv_pres *srv_pres,
630  pjsua_buddy_id buddy_id,
631  const pj_str_t *from,
632  pjsip_rx_data *rdata,
633  pjsip_status_code *code,
634  pj_str_t *reason,
635  pjsua_msg_data *msg_data_)

829 static void on_transport_state(pjsip_transport *tp,

905 #endif

1131 /*
1132  * A simple registrar, invoked by default_mod_on_rx_request()
1133  */
1134 static void simple_registrar(pjsip_rx_data *rdata)
1135 {
1136  pjsip_tx_data *tdata;
1137  const pjsip_expires_hdr *exp;
1138  const pjsip_hdr *h;
1139  unsigned cnt = 0;
1140  pjsip_generic_string_hdr *srv;
1141  pj_status_t status;
1142 
1143  status = pjsip_endpt_create_response(pjsua_get_pjsip_endpt(),
1144  rdata, 200, NULL, &tdata);
1145  if (status != PJ_SUCCESS)
1146  return;
1147 
1148  exp = (pjsip_expires_hdr *)pjsip_msg_find_hdr(rdata->msg_info.msg,
1149  PJSIP_H_EXPIRES, NULL);
1150 
1151  h = rdata->msg_info.msg->hdr.next;
1152  while (h != &rdata->msg_info.msg->hdr) {
1153  if (h->type == PJSIP_H_CONTACT) {
1154  const pjsip_contact_hdr *c = (const pjsip_contact_hdr*)h;
1155  unsigned e = c->expires;
1156 
1157  if (e != PJSIP_EXPIRES_NOT_SPECIFIED) {
1158  if (exp)
1159  e = exp->ivalue;
1160  else
1161  e = 3600;
1162  }
1163 
1164  if (e > 0) {
1165  pjsip_contact_hdr *nc = (pjsip_contact_hdr *)pjsip_hdr_clone(
1166  tdata->pool, h);
1167  nc->expires = e;
1168  pjsip_msg_add_hdr(tdata->msg, (pjsip_hdr*)nc);
1169  ++cnt;
1170  }
1171  }
1172  h = h->next;
1173  }
1174 
1175  srv = pjsip_generic_string_hdr_create(tdata->pool, NULL, NULL);
1176  srv->name = pj_str("Server");
1177  srv->hvalue = pj_str("pjsua simple registrar");
1178  pjsip_msg_add_hdr(tdata->msg, (pjsip_hdr*)srv);
1179 
1180  status = pjsip_endpt_send_response2(pjsua_get_pjsip_endpt(),
1181  rdata, tdata, NULL, NULL);
1182  if (status != PJ_SUCCESS) {
1183  pjsip_tx_data_dec_ref(tdata);
1184  }
1185 
1186 }

1188 /*****************************************************************************
1189  * A simple module to handle otherwise unhandled request. We will register
1190  * this with the lowest priority.
1191  */
1192 
1193 /* Notification on incoming request */
1194 static pj_bool_t default_mod_on_rx_request(pjsip_rx_data *rdata)
1195 {
1196  pjsip_tx_data *tdata;
1197  pjsip_status_code status_code;
1198  pj_status_t status;
1199 
1200  /* Don't respond to ACK! */
1201  if (pjsip_method_cmp(&rdata->msg_info.msg->line.req.method,
1202  &pjsip_ack_method) == 0)
1203  return PJ_TRUE;
1204 
1205  /* Simple registrar */
1206  if (pjsip_method_cmp(&rdata->msg_info.msg->line.req.method,
1207  &pjsip_register_method) == 0)
1208  {
1209  simple_registrar(rdata);
1210  return PJ_TRUE;
1211  }
1212 
1213  /* Create basic response. */
1214  if (pjsip_method_cmp(&rdata->msg_info.msg->line.req.method,
1215  &pjsip_notify_method) == 0)
1216  {
1217  /* Unsolicited NOTIFY's, send with Bad Request */
1218  status_code = PJSIP_SC_BAD_REQUEST;
1219  } else {
1220  /* Probably unknown method */
1221  status_code = PJSIP_SC_METHOD_NOT_ALLOWED;
1222  }
1223  status = pjsip_endpt_create_response(pjsua_get_pjsip_endpt(),
1224  rdata, status_code,
1225  NULL, &tdata);
1226  if (status != PJ_SUCCESS) {
1227  pjsua_perror(THIS_FILE, "Unable to create response", status);
1228  return PJ_TRUE;
1229  }
1230 
1231  /* Add Allow if we're responding with 405 */
1232  if (status_code == PJSIP_SC_METHOD_NOT_ALLOWED) {
1233  const pjsip_hdr *cap_hdr;

1989  }

1995  call_opt.aud_cnt = app_config.aud_cnt;
1996  call_opt.vid_cnt = app_config.vid.vid_cnt;
1997

1999  NULL, NULL);

2003

2005  cli_main(wait_telnet_cli);

2147  * arrange the attachment to the PJSUA-LIB conference bridge as such

2149  * slot 0 in the bridge, and channel1/right channel of the sound

2155  *
